      • sreed_window

        public static int sreed_window(java.lang.String tag,
               int n_dim,
               int[] n_cube,
               int[] n_wind,
               int[] f_wind,
               int[] j_wind,
               int esize,
               byte[] vals)
        Read window from seplib input file.
        Parameters:
        tag - The tag (or name), e.g. "in", for the seplib input file.
        n_dim - The number of dimensions in input seplib dataset.
        n_cube - Vector[n_dim] of input axis lengths.
        n_wind - Vector[n_dim] of cube axis lengths after windowing.
        f_wind - Vector[n_dim] of first element for windowing (0 <= f < n)
        j_wind - Vector[n_dim] of subsample rate for windowing (1 <= j < n)
        esize - Number of bytes per element.
        vals - Array to contain data to be read from input.
        Returns:
        0 if success, -2 for bad window params, -1 otherwise Note: For byte[] arrays, esize can be larger than 1
